theorem Topology.preimage_interior_subset_interior_preimage
    {X Y : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] [TopologicalSpace Y] {f : X → Y}
    (hf : Continuous f) {S : Set Y} :
    f ⁻¹' interior (S : Set Y) ⊆ interior (f ⁻¹' S) := by
  intro x hx
  -- The set `V := f ⁻¹' interior S` is an open neighbourhood of `x`.
  have hV_open : IsOpen (f ⁻¹' interior (S : Set Y)) :=
    (isOpen_interior : IsOpen (interior (S : Set Y))).preimage hf
  -- Moreover, `V` is contained in `f ⁻¹' S`.
  have hV_subset : (f ⁻¹' interior (S : Set Y) : Set X) ⊆ f ⁻¹' S := by
    intro y hy
    exact interior_subset hy
  -- Apply the maximality property of the interior with the open neighbourhood `V`.
  exact (interior_maximal hV_subset hV_open) hx
